jobs.description:
Main Responsibilities 
 Business Risk – Assist with implementing the Bank’s Suitability Framework, creating the relevant procedures and guides, providing training on documents and systems relevant to suitability and guiding the Front Office on best practices. 
 Business Monitoring – Assist with implementing procedures and control solutions and monitoring business activities to ensure compliant Front Office & Client Documentation staff and activities, providing assurance on the quality of the controls and tasks performed. Conducting investigations in relation to procedural and control issues and leading associated remediation activity. 
 Role Duties 
 Key Accountabilities 

 General : 
 Maintain a Group-wide and ‘team’ perspective in project leadership and business support activities, balancing commercial and control requirements whilst recognising location differences where they need to be applied; 

 Comply with external regulatory and internal policy requirements, including the Bank’s global and regional Directives, Policies, Operating Procedures and controls to meet the Bank’s local regulatory requirements and to protect the business from financial, regulatory and reputational risk; 


 Quality Assurance, Monitoring and Oversight : 
 Monitor Private Banking and Client Documentation processes and activities, seeking continuous improvement and assuring quality; 

 Perform assurance testing on key aspects of risk and controls; 

 Review / Monitor defined activities in conjunction with Risk / Compliance; 

 Monitor Private Banking and Client Documentation rectification of document deficiencies or completion of remediation project work; 

 Assist with completing the Team’s Management & Functional Controls; 

 Review and approve, where appropriate, exceptions to processes and re-tagging of clients; 


 Procedures & Controls Implementation: 
 Assist with reviewing and agreeing local Directives and Policies; 

 Review and implement User Guides and Key Operating Procedures for key Front Office and Client Documentation processes; 

 Assist with implementing and reviewing the Management & Functional Controls (MFCs) for the London Private Banking business; 

 Agree specifications and provide support for testing and sign off for implementation of PB Portal / other systems enhancements; 

 Provide input to, or represent, Private Banking in operational / regulatory initiatives or projects; 

 Collaborate with support functions (e.g. Risk, Operations) on compliance, loss prevention and workplace efficiency; 

 Find and implement solutions for ad-hoc queries from Private Banking staff. 


 Audits / Investigations and Remediation: 
 Investigate and report on operational issues / errors and ensure client complaints are escalated; 

 Provide monthly management information for specified risk items to Risk for presentation at the London Compliance & Risk Committee / Management Committee for management oversight and review with relevant stakeholders; 

 Assist with the production of client data lists, and analysis in response to audit comments and audit points; 

 Assist with the remediation of any open audit points to closure; 

 Follow up on risk issues logged in the risk database owned by Private Banking. 


 Training : 
 Support the development of training guides on key business processes to assist in improving knowledge and reducing operational errors; 

 Contribute to / deliver relevant regulatory / internal training to ensure competent and compliant staff and activities; 

 Deliver relevant induction training for all new staff within Wealth Management. 


 The job description is not exhaustive and may include other duties as assigned from time to time by Line Manager and Management. 

 Committee Membership 
 None 

 Conduct Rules 
 This role is required to comply with the Financial Conduct Authority’s (FCA) Individual Conduct Rules, which are: 

 To act with integrity; 
 To act with due skill, care and diligence; 
 To be open and cooperative with the FCA, the Prudential Regulation Authoritity (PRA) and other regulators; 
 To pay due regard to the interests of customers and treat them fairly; 
 To observe proper standards of market conduct; and 
 To act to deliver good outcomes for retail customers. 
 Person Specification 
 Knowledge, Skills & Experience 

 Qualifications: 
 Completion of UBP Annual Compliance training programme 

 Critical Competencies: skills and abilities required for the role: 
 Strong understanding of UBP systems and procedures, 

 Strong understanding of risk management principles and tools; 

 Strong understanding of local regulatory requirements; 

 Strong understanding of business processes and associated controls within financial institutions, preferably within Private Banking; 

 Strong organisational and attention to detail skills, with the ability to handle multiple tasks and meet deadlines; 

 Strong communication, stakeholder engagement and relationship building skills with key stakeholders; 

 Strong analytical and problem solving skills; 

 Strong management and project management / co-ordination skills; 

 Strong understanding of Microsoft Office Applications, in particular Excel. 

 Competencies and Values Required

Mission 
 Ensure detection and monitoring of high-risk transactions in an AML perspective and in respect of applicable laws and regulations as well as internal policies and procedures. Execute other Compliance controls and monitoring tasks.

 Main responsibilities 
 Perform second level of control on high-risk alerts generated by the transaction monitoring system to identify suspicious activities and potential financial crime risks;
 Assess completeness and accuracy of the RM explanations on AML alerts and analyze plausibility of information and supportive documentation on file;
 Carry out additional clarifications and investigations on suspicious payments or patterns;
 Review transaction requests and manage daily operations on blocked accounts;
 Periodical review of blockages’ reasons and necessity;
 Provide guidance, training, support and relevant information to Relationship Managers on daily basis;
 Liaise with relevant stakeholders such as Compliance Market Expert, Business Risk Manager, Legal, Risk, Credit Department, and Operations, to ensure a holistic approach;
 Prepare internal memorandums and present the case to the dedicated committee when required;
 Provide recommendations for enhancing monitoring processes and assist with Compliance projects and initiatives.

 Your Profile 
 Degree in Law, Economics, Finance, Business Administration or equivalent.
 A minimum of 2 years’ experience as Compliance, KYC and AML in Private Banking or similar role;
 In-depth knowledge of banking processes, operations, products and systems, AML and sanctions;
 Capacity to deal with several matters simultaneously;
 Ability to work independently, take decisions and set priorities;
 Pragmatic and solution oriented;
 Strong analytical and communication skills;
 Fluent in French and English; additional languages are considered an asset;
 Adherence to the company’s values: Dedication, Conviction, Agility and Responsibility.

 Others 
 Swiss Residence: Mandatory

 Core Competencies : Adherence to the company’s values: Dedication, Conviction, Agility and Responsibility - Compliance with regulations and internal directives
